bitfields.name: ENB_DIR_ACC_CTLR_FLD
bitfields.ldesc: Enable Direct Access Controller: 0 : disable the Direct Access Controller once current transfer of the data word [FF_W] is complete. 1 : enable the Direct Access Controller When the Direct Access Controller and Indirect Access Controller are both disabled, all AHB requested are completed with an error response.
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x1
Bitfield Offset: 7
CONFIG_REG Register Address: 0xfc40000
CONFIG_REG Register Reset Value: 0x80780081
Register Description: Octal-SPI Configuration Register
Bitfield Description: Enable Direct Access Controller - 0 - disable the Direct Access Controller once current transfer of the data word [FF_W] is complete. 1 - enable the Direct Access Controller When the Direct Access Controller and Indirect Access Controller are both disabled, all AHB requested are completed with an error response.

bitfields.name: ENB_SPI_FLD
bitfields.ldesc: Octal-SPI Enable: 0 : disable the Octal-SPI, once current transfer of the data word [FF_W] is complete. 1 : enable the Octal-SPI, when spi_enable = 0, all output enables are inactive and all pins are set to input mode.
bitfields.description:

Register Description: Octal-SPI Configuration Register
Bitfield Description: Octal-SPI Enable - 0 - disable the Octal-SPI, once current transfer of the data word [FF_W] is complete. 1 - enable the Octal-SPI, when spi_enable = 0, all output enables are inactive and all pins are set to input mode.

value equal to or greater that post_div2. Supports values of 1-7i

 3'b010 - Divide by 2
 3'b011 - Divide by 3

bitfields.name: FB_DIV_INT
bitfields.ldesc:
PLL feedback divider (integer portion)
 In Integer mode values of 16 - 3200 (dec) are supported.
 In Fractional mode values of 20 to 320 are supported.
 12'h010 - Divide by 16
 12'h011 - Divide by 17
 :
 12'h140 - Divide by 320
 : 12'hC80 - Divide by 3200
 12'hC81 - 12'hFFF - Not supported
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x10
Bitfield Offset: 0
PLL0_FREQ_CTRL0 Register Address: 0x4040030
PLL0_FREQ_CTRL0 Register Reset Value: 0x10
Register Description: PLL0_FREQ_CTRL0 - PLL0 Frequency Control 0 Register
Bitfield Description: PLL feedback divider (integer portion)  In Integer mode values of 16 - 3200 (dec) are supported.  In Fractional mode values of 20 to 320 are supported.
:  12'h010 - Divide by 16
: 12'h011 - Divide by 17
:  12'h140 - Divide by 320
 : 12'hC80 - Divide by 3200
: 12'hC81 - 12'hFFF - Not supported

bitfields.name: FB_DIV_FRAC
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x0
Bitfield Offset: 0
PLL0_FREQ_CTRL1 Register Address: 0x4040034
PLL0_FREQ_CTRL1 Register Reset Value: 0x0
Register Description: PLL0_FREQ_CTRL1 - PLL0 Frequency Control 1 Register
Bitfield Description: PLL feedback divider (fractional portion)  Supports values of 0 to 0.999999940395. The total feedback divide value is (fb_div_int + fb_div_frac / (2^24))
:  24'h000000 - 0
: 24'h000001 - .000000059605 (1/(2^24))
:  24'h000002 - .000000119209 (2/(2^24)) 
:  24'h800000 - .500000000000
 : 24'hFFFFFF - .999999940395 (1677215/(2^24))

ipInstances.longDescription:
Output | Description | Frequency

--- | --- | ---

FOUTP | Positive phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTN | Negative phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTPOSTDIV | VCO-divided clock output | FOUTP / (POST_DIV1*POST_DIV2)

CLKSSCG | Clock to SSMOD | (FREF / REF_DIV)

inPins.name: csi_rx_byte_clk
inPins.description: byte_clk is the clock supplied by the dphy_rx pll and is divided down to byte clock. the dphy_rx is designed for max of 10gbps. this translates to a max byte clock of 312.5mhz. the clock is inactive when dphy_rx is not in hs operation

bitfields.ldesc:

 :

:  12'h140 - Divide by 320

: 12'hC81 - 12'hFFF - Not supported

Bitfield Description: PLL feedback divider (fractional portion)  Supports values of 0 to 0.999999940395. The total feedback divide value is (fb_div_int + fb_div_frac / (2^24))
:  24'h000000 - 0
: 24'h000001 - .000000059605 (1/(2^24))
:  24'h000002 - .000000119209 (2/(2^24)) 
:  24'h800000 - .500000000000

ipInstances.longDescription:
Output | Description | Frequency

--- | --- | ---

FOUTP | Positive phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTN | Negative phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTPOSTDIV | VCO-divided clock output | FOUTP / (POST_DIV1*POST_DIV2)

CLKSSCG | Clock to SSMOD | (FREF / REF_DIV)

bitfields.ldesc:
Primary post divider. To ensure correct operation, post_div1 must always be programmed to a
value equal to or greater that post_div2. Supports values of 1-7i

 Field values (Others are reserved):
 3'b000 - Reserved (do not use)
 3'b001 - Divide by 1
 3'b010 - Divide by 2
 3'b011 - Divide by 3
 3'b100 - Divide by 4
 3'b101 - Divide by 5
 3'b110 - Divide by 6
 3'b111 - Divide by 7
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x2
Bitfield Offset: 16
PLL12_DIV_CTRL Register Address: 0x68c038
PLL12_DIV_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x1020001
Register Description: PLL12_DIV_CTRL - PLL12 Output Clock Divider Register
Bitfield Description: Primary post divider. To ensure correct operation, post_div1 must always be programmed to a value equal to or greater that post_div2. Supports values of 1-7i 
  Field values (Others are reserved):  3'b000 - Reserved (do not use)
:  3'b001 - Divide by 1
: 3'b010 - Divide by 2
: 3'b011 - Divide by 3
: 3'b100 - Divide by 4
: 3'b101 - Divide by 5
: 3'b110 - Divide by 6
: 3'b111 - Divide by 7

bitfields.ldesc: Secondary post divider. Supports values of 1-7

Bitfield Offset: 24

PLL12_DIV_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x1020001
Register Description: PLL12_DIV_CTRL - PLL12 Output Clock Divider Register
Bitfield Description: Secondary post divider. Supports values of 1-7

bitfields.name: REF_DIV
bitfields.ldesc:
Reference clock pre-divider. Supports values of 1-63
 6'b000000 - Reserved /(do not use/)
 6'b000001 - Divide by 1
 6'b000010 - Divide by 2
 :
 6'b111111 - Divide by 63
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x1
Bitfield Offset: 0
PLL12_DIV_CTRL Register Address: 0x68c038
PLL12_DIV_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x1020001
Register Description: PLL12_DIV_CTRL - PLL12 Output Clock Divider Register
Bitfield Description: Reference clock pre-divider. Supports values of 1-63
: 6'b000000 - Reserved (do not use)
:  6'b000001 - Divide by 1
: 6'b000010 - Divide by 2
:  6'b111111 - Divide by 63

bitfields.name: FB_DIV_INT
bitfields.ldesc:
PLL feedback divider (integer portion)
 In Integer mode values of 16 - 3200 (dec) are supported.
 In Fractional mode values of 20 to 320 are supported.
 12'h010 - Divide by 16
 12'h011 - Divide by 17
 :
 12'h140 - Divide by 320
 : 12'hC80 - Divide by 3200
 12'hC81 - 12'hFFF - Not supported
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x10
Bitfield Offset: 0
PLL12_FREQ_CTRL0 Register Address: 0x68c030
PLL12_FREQ_CTRL0 Register Reset Value: 0x10
Register Description: PLL0_FREQ_CTRL0 - PLL12 Frequency Control 12 Register
Bitfield Description: PLL feedback divider (integer portion)  In Integer mode values of 16 - 3200 (dec) are supported.  In Fractional mode values of 20 to 320 are supported.
:  12'h010 - Divide by 16
: 12'h011 - Divide by 17
:  12'h140 - Divide by 320
 : 12'hC80 - Divide by 3200
: 12'hC81 - 12'hFFF - Not supported

bitfields.name: FB_DIV_FRAC
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x0
Bitfield Offset: 0
PLL12_FREQ_CTRL1 Register Address: 0x68c034
PLL12_FREQ_CTRL1 Register Reset Value: 0x0
Register Description: PLL12_FREQ_CTRL1 - PLL0 Frequency Control 1 Register
Bitfield Description: PLL feedback divider (fractional portion)  Supports values of 0 to 0.999999940395. The total feedback divide value is (fb_div_int + fb_div_frac / (2^24))
:  24'h000000 - 0
: 24'h000001 - .000000059605 (1/(2^24))
:  24'h000002 - .000000119209 (2/(2^24)) 
:  24'h800000 - .500000000000
 : 24'hFFFFFF - .999999940395 (1677215/(2^24))

:1'b1 - SSMOD is bypassed. No modulation of PLL frequency

:1'b1 - Use external wave table

bitfields.name: SPREAD
bitfields.ldesc:

:
5'b10000 - 1.6%

:5'b11111 - 3.1%

bitfields.name: BYPASS_EN
bitfields.ldesc:
Bypass enable. This controls the glitch-free bypass mux. The bypass_en bit should be set prior tomaking any changes to the PLL settings.
 1'b0 - Synchronously select PLL and associated HSDIV clock outputs
 1'b1 - Synchronously select the reference clock for all PLL and HSDIV clock outputs
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x1
Bitfield Offset: 31
PLL12_CTRL Register Address: 0x68c020
PLL12_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x80010011

Bitfield Description: Bypass enable. This controls the glitch-free bypass mux. The bypass_en bit should be set prior tomaking any changes to the PLL settings.
:  1'b0 - Synchronously select PLL and associated HSDIV clock outputs
:  1'b1 - Synchronously select the reference clock for all PLL and HSDIV clock outputs

bitfields.name: CLK_POSTDIV_EN
bitfields.ldesc:
Post divide CLK enable
 1'b0 - Post divide powered down. FOUTPOSTDIV and all auxiliary PLL clocks (4-ohase and
synchronous divided clocks) are held low
 1'b1 - Post divide enabled. FOUTPOSTDIV, 4-phase and synchronous clocks are enabled.
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x1
Bitfield Offset: 4
PLL12_CTRL Register Address: 0x68c020
PLL12_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x80010011
Register Description: PLL12_CTRL - PLL12 Control
Bitfield Description: Post divide CLK enable
:  1'b0 - Post divide powered down. FOUTPOSTDIV and all auxiliary PLL clocks (4-ohase and synchronous divided clocks) are held low
:  1'b1 - Post divide enabled. FOUTPOSTDIV, 4-phase and synchronous clocks are enabled.

bitfields.name: DAC_EN
bitfields.ldesc:
Enable fractional noise canceling DAC
This bit has no function (DAC is always disabled) in integer divide mode (when dsm_en=0)
 1'b0 - Fractional NC DAC is disabled (for Test modes only)
 1'b1 - Fractional NC DAC is enabled (ignored in integer divide mode)
bitfields.description:
Bitfield Reset Value: 0x1
Bitfield Offset: 0
PLL12_CTRL Register Address: 0x68c020
PLL12_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x80010011
Register Description: PLL12_CTRL - PLL12 Control

:  1'b0 - Fractional NC DAC is disabled (for Test modes only)
:  1'b1 - Fractional NC DAC is enabled (ignored in integer divide mode)

bitfields.name: DSM_EN
bitfields.ldesc:
Delta-Sigma modulator enable
 1'b0 - Delta-Sigma modulator is disabled (use integer divide mode)
 1'b1 - Delta-Sigma modulator is enabled (use fractional divide mode)

Bitfield Reset Value: 0x0
Bitfield Offset: 1

PLL12_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x80010011
Register Description: PLL12_CTRL - PLL12 Control
Bitfield Description: Delta-Sigma modulator enable
:  1'b0 - Delta-Sigma modulator is disabled (use integer divide mode)
:  1'b1 - Delta-Sigma modulator is enabled (use fractional divide mode)

bitfields.name: PLL_EN

 1'b0 - PLL is disabled
 1'b1 - PLL is enabled

Bitfield Offset: 15

PLL12_CTRL Register Reset Value: 0x80010011
Register Description: PLL12_CTRL - PLL12 Control
Bitfield Description: PLL enable

Partition12 registers

bitfields.name: UNLOCKED
bitfields.ldesc:
Unlock status.
  When set, indicates that the proper unlock sequence has been performed and the partition is
unlocked for writing.

Bitfield Offset: 0

Register Description: PLL12_LOCKKEY0 - PLL12 Lock Key 0 Register

registers

Bitfield Offset: 0

Bitfield Description: Write the kick1 unlock value after the kick0 unlock value to unlock the write-protected Partition12
registers

ipInstances.longDescription:
Output | Description | Frequency

--- | --- | ---

FOUTP | Positive phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTN | Negative phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTPOSTDIV | VCO-divided clock output | FOUTP / (POST_DIV1*POST_DIV2)

CLKSSCG | Clock to SSMOD | (FREF / REF_DIV)

:  1'b1 - Synchronously select the reference clock for all PLL and HSDIV clock outputs

bitfields.name: CLK_POSTDIV_EN
bitfields.ldesc:
Post divide CLK enable
 1'b0 - Post divide powered down. FOUTPOSTDIV and all auxiliary PLL clocks (4-ohase and
synchronous divided clocks) are held low
 1'b1 - Post divide enabled. FOUTPOSTDIV, 4-phase and synchronous clocks are enabled.
bitfields.description:

Bitfield Offset: 4
PLL8_CTRL Register Address: 0x688020

Register Description: PLL8_CTRL - PLL8 Control
Bitfield Description: Post divide CLK enable
:  1'b0 - Post divide powered down. FOUTPOSTDIV and all auxiliary PLL clocks (4-ohase and synchronous divided clocks) are held low
:  1'b1 - Post divide enabled. FOUTPOSTDIV, 4-phase and synchronous clocks are enabled.

bitfields.name: DAC_EN
bitfields.ldesc:
Enable fractional noise canceling DAC
This bit has no function (DAC is always disabled) in integer divide mode (when dsm_en=0)
 1'b0 - Fractional NC DAC is disabled (for Test modes only)
 1'b1 - Fractional NC DAC is enabled (ignored in integer divide mode)

bitfields.name: DSM_EN

ipInstances.longDescription:
Output | Description | Frequency

--- | --- | ---

FOUTP | Positive phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTN | Negative phase VCO output (no post divider) | (FREF / REF_DIV) * (FB_DIV + FB_DIV_FRAC)

FOUTPOSTDIV | VCO-divided clock output | FOUTP / (POST_DIV1*POST_DIV2)

CLKSSCG | Clock to SSMOD | (FREF / REF_DIV)
